The minister lodged an urgent application to suspend and interdict the remedial orders by the Public Protector, citing 'improper motives' on her part. Editor's note: Livestream courtesy DStv 403, you can also watch it on DStv Now JOHANNESBURG - The North Gauteng High Court is handing down its judgment in the matter between Public Enterprises Minister, Pravin Gordhan and Public Protector, Busisiwe Mkhwebane. The minister lodged an urgent application to suspend and interdict the remedial orders by the Public Protector, citing 'improper motives' on her part. Mkhwebane found the minister broke the law when he established the intelligence unit at the revenue service. She's directed President Cyril Ramaphosa to take disciplinary action against Gordhan.